HEADWORD: Geocronite
<hw>Ge*oc"ro*nite</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>n.</pos> <ety>[Gr.
<grk>ge`a</grk>, <grk>gh^</grk>, the earth + <grk>Kro`nos</grk> Saturn,
the alchemistic name of lead: cf. G. <ets>geokronit</ets>.]</ety>
<fld>(Min.)</fld> <def>A lead-gray or grayish blue mineral with a
metallic luster, consisting of sulphur, antimony, and lead, with a small
proportion of arsenic.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Geocyclic</ent>⟦br⟧
